1. Arduino UNO

Function: Main controller

Reads sensors
Controls motor
Sends data to Serial Monitor
2. Motor Driver (L298N)

Function: Drives DC motor using external power

Connections:
ENA → D6
IN1 → D9
IN2 → D7
GND → Arduino GND + all grounds
12V → Adapter + (through ACS712)
OUT1 → Motor wire 1
OUT2 → Motor wire 2
Function:
Controls motor speed (ENA PWM)
Controls direction (IN1, IN2)
Stops motor when IR detects object
3. IR Sensor

Function: Detects object on conveyor

Connections:
VCC → 5V
GND → GND
OUT → D13
Function:
Output changes when object is detected
Used to stop/start motor
4. Load Cell + HX711

Function: Measures weight

HX711 → Arduino:
VCC → 5V
GND → GND
DT → D3
SCK → D2
Load Cell → HX711:
Red → E+
Black → E-
White → A-
Green → A+
Function:
Converts strain into digital weight values
5. ACS712 Current Sensor

Function: Measures motor current

Connections:
VCC → 5V
GND → GND
OUT → A0
Power Path:
Adapter + → ACS712 → L298N 12V
Function:
Detects current used by motor
6. Power Supply (12V Adapter)

Function: Powers motor only

Connections:
Red (+) → ACS712 → L298N 12V
Black (−) → L298N GND
7. Jumper Wires

Function: Connect all components

Used for:
Signal connections (D2, D3, D6, D7, D9, D13, A0)
Power (5V, GND)
Communication between modules
Important:
Male-to-female jumper wires used
All GND must be connected together
COMMON GROUND (VERY IMPORTANT)

Connect all GND together:

Arduino GND
L298N GND
IR Sensor GND
HX711 GND
ACS712 GND
Adapter negative
Overall Working Flow

Object placed → IR detects → Motor stops → Load cell measures weight → ACS712 measures current → Serial Monitor displays data

Final Features
Automatic object detection
Motor control (ON/OFF)
Weight measurement
Current monitoring
External motor power
Full sensor integration
Serial Monitor output
